            were since I was introduced to the Edhi Centre when I was just 2
            years old. My memories are faint, but I recall someone bringing me
            to the center. I've lived happily at the Edhi Centre ever since.
            Despite efforts by the Edhi organization to find my biological
            parents, they were unsuccessful. Now, at 27 years old, my life
            revolves around the Edhi Foundation. Mr. Abdul Sattar Edhi and Mrs.
            Bilqees Edhi have been like parents to me. I'm immensely grateful
            for their care and support during my time at the Edhi Centre. <br
            /><br /> Thanks to them, I am now married and have a daughter. The Edhi
            organization never let me feel alone; they provided warmth and affection
            always. I'm unable to fully express my gratitude for their kindness and
            assistance.
          </p>
